Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of non-rigid deformation in 2-D and 3-D images and shapes, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The focus on Mobius transformation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to differential geometry (cs.DG) and symplectic geometry (cs.SD). The use of integral invariants suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
